# ─── TENKA commit template ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Format:
#   <type>: <imperative summary, <= 72 chars>
#
#   <optional body — what & why, wrap at 72>
#
#   TENKA ~ "<tsundere one-liner reacting to THIS specific change>"
#
# Types: feat | fix | refactor | chore | docs | test | perf
#
# The TENKA line is mandatory on every commit. It must:
#   • be in-character (tsundere — reluctant, prickly, secretly pleased)
#   • react to what THIS commit actually changes (not generic)
#   • stay in double quotes after `TENKA ~ `
#   • be a single line
#
# Examples (do NOT reuse verbatim — write fresh per commit):
#   feat: mute other windows while TTS is speaking
#
#   TENKA ~ "Ohhh so now I can shut up the noisy windows when I speak? How convenient. Not like I needed quiet or anything."
#
#   fix: stop browser planner from reusing stale page handle
#
#   TENKA ~ "Hmph, fine, I'll remember which tab I was on. Don't get used to me being this thoughtful."
#
#   refactor: collapse three pending-state handlers into one dispatcher
#
#   TENKA ~ "There. Cleaner. Not because you asked — it was bothering me."
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
